Date:  0/0/1889
Source:  Art Album NZ Flora
Author:  FEATON
Vol / Page:  32
Edition:
Quote:  PITTOSPORUM TENUIFOLIUM (<i>Banks & Sol</i>.) ... This small evergreen tree, known by the native names of `Kowhiwhi' and `Maupariki', abounds on the eastern coasts of both Islands. ... Even as firewood it is despised, and bears the all too suggestive name of `Bucket of Water Wood', so little is it calculated by its combustive qualities to enliven the domestic hearth. <i>IBid.</i> 178 Maupariki [Maori name] .. Kowhiwhi [Settlers' name] .. Pittosporum tenuifolium .. Small tree
